tp://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ourPrivacy notice\", \"from\": 383, \"to\": 400}, {\"ngram\": \"the2024 Olympicsin full swing\", \"from\": 406, \"to\": 435}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 459, \"to\": 471}, {\"ngram\": \"training\", \"from\": 506, \"to\": 514}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the event only happens once every four years, the Olympians are also taking the opportunity to participate in various traditions that are meant to commemorate what they spend their entire lives working to achieve.\", \"from\": 518, \"to\": 734, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 521, \"to\": 530}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympians\", \"from\": 567, \"to\": 580}, {\"ngram\": \"the opportunity\", \"from\": 597, \"to\": 612}, {\"ngram\": \"various traditions\", \"from\": 631, \"to\": 649}, {\"ngram\": \"their entire lives\", \"from\": 696, \"to\": 714}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Although the traditions may appear unconventional, most of them date back decades.\", \"from\": 735, \"to\": 817, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the traditions\", \"from\": 744, \"to\": 758}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Similar to the pin-trading tradition in the Disney theme parks, the Olympic athletes also participate in pin-trading in the Olympic Village.\", \"from\": 819, \"to\": 959, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 863, \"end\": 869, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Walt_Disney_Company\", \"score\": 0.9999994495616799, \"rank\": 3.7607272934107323e-07, \"text\": \"Disney\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Walt_Disney_Company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Walt_Disney_Company\"}, {\"begin\": 943, \"end\": 958, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.963418270861344e-21, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the pin-trading tradition\", \"from\": 830, \"to\": 855}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic athletes\", \"from\": 883, \"to\": 903}, {\"ngram\": \"pin-trading\", \"from\": 924, \"to\": 935}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The tradition dates back to one of the first Olympic games in Athens in 1896, when the Greeks would be presented with cloth pins featuring a competing country's national anthem.\", \"from\": 960, \"to\": 1137, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1022, \"end\": 1028, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999997064042394, \"rank\": 2.935957705744378e-07, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1047, \"end\": 1053, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"score\": 0.5909994778067416, \"rank\": 0.6539038583331045, \"text\": \"Greeks\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The tradition\", \"from\": 960, \"to\": 973}, {\"ngram\": \"the first Olympic games\", \"from\": 995, \"to\": 1018}, {\"ngram\": \"cloth pins\", \"from\": 1078, \"to\": 1088}, {\"ngram\": \"a competing country's national anthem\", \"from\": 1099, \"to\": 1136}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Every year, there are new pins designed by countries, the teams' themselves, or a brand sponsor.\", \"from\": 1139, \"to\": 1235, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"new pins\", \"from\": 1161, \"to\": 1169}, {\"ngram\": \"countries\", \"from\": 1182, \"to\": 1191}, {\"ngram\": \"the teams' themselves\", \"from\": 1193, \"to\": 1214}, {\"ngram\": \"a brand sponsor\", \"from\": 1219, \"to\": 1234}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The tradition was first reserved for only the athletes, but currently anyone attending the games can receive a lanyard to fill up with different pins.\", \"from\": 1236, \"to\": 1386, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The tradition\", \"from\": 1236, \"to\": 1249}, {\"ngram\": \"only the athletes\", \"from\": 1273, \"to\": 1290}, {\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 1306, \"to\": 1312}, {\"ngram\": \"the games\", \"from\": 1323, \"to\": 1332}, {\"ngram\": \"a lanyard\", \"from\": 1345, \"to\": 1354}, {\"ngram\": \"different pins\", \"from\": 1371, \"to\": 1385}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On social media, Olympians have begun showing off their collections, with notable collectors this year including American rugby player Ilona Maher and Danish tennis player Caroline Wozniacki.\", \"from\": 1388, \"to\": 1579, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1501, \"end\": 1509, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999966896962125, \"rank\": 1.6902190944410343e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1523, \"end\": 1534, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ilona_Maher\", \"score\": 0.9999999134151987, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ilona Maher\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ilona_Maher\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ilona_Maher\"}, {\"begin\": 1539, \"end\": 1545, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Danish_language\", \"score\": 0.6202702527293643, \"rank\": 0.6072314213198342, \"text\": \"Danish\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Danish_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Danish_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1560, \"end\": 1578, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caroline_Wozniacki\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Caroline Wozniacki\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caroline_Wozniacki\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Caroline_Wozniacki\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"social media\", \"from\": 1391, \"to\": 1403}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympians\", \"from\": 1405, \"to\": 1414}, {\"ngram\": \"their collections\", \"from\": 1438, \"to\": 1455}, {\"ngram\": \"notable collectors\", \"from\": 1462, \"to\": 1480}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For some athletes, they want to make sure their experience in the games is one that they never forget, which is why viewers will notice some of the Olympians have the five Olympic Rings tattooed somewhere on their body.\", \"from\": 1581, \"to\": 1800, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some athletes\", \"from\": 1585, \"to\": 1598}, {\"ngram\": \"their experience\", \"from\": 1623, \"to\": 1639}, {\"ngram\": \"the games\", \"from\": 1643, \"to\": 1652}, {\"ngram\": \"viewers\", \"from\": 1697, \"to\": 1704}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympians\", \"from\": 1725, \"to\": 1738}, {\"ngram\": \"the five Olympic Rings tattooed\", \"from\": 1744, \"to\": 1775}, {\"ngram\": \"their body\", \"from\": 1789, \"to\": 1799}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chris Jacobs, a swimmer who won three medals at the 1988 Summer Olympics in Seoul, is the athleteknown for first starting this traditionafter noticing some of the Canadian swimmers around him with tattoos of their nation's flag.\", \"from\": 1802, \"to\": 2030, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1802, \"end\": 1814, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Jacobs_(politician)\", \"score\": 0.8448246122939471, \"rank\": 0.1571980143408498, \"text\": \"Chris Jacobs\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Jacobs_(politician)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Jacobs_(politician)\"}, {\"begin\": 1878, \"end\": 1883, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999998453699965, \"rank\": 1.5462986921837518e-07, \"text\": \"Seoul\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1988_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1965, \"end\": 1973, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.9830989859489595, \"rank\": 0.016603110869368706, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a swimmer\", \"from\": 1816, \"to\": 1825}, {\"ngram\": \"three medals\", \"from\": 1834, \"to\": 1846}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1988 Summer Olympics\", \"from\": 1850, \"to\": 1874}, {\"ngram\": \"the athleteknown\", \"from\": 1888, \"to\": 1904}, {\"ngram\": \"this traditionafter\", \"from\": 1924, \"to\": 1943}, {\"ngram\": \"tattoos\", \"from\": 1999, \"to\": 2006}, {\"ngram\": \"their nation's flag\", \"from\": 2010, \"to\": 2029}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Although Jacobs' original version of the ink was small and hidden by his bathing suit, he gradually made it bigger and placed it on his bicep.\", \"from\": 2031, \"to\": 2173, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Jacobs' original version\", \"from\": 2040, \"to\": 2064}, {\"ngram\": \"the ink\", \"from\": 2068, \"to\": 2075}, {\"ngram\": \"his bathing suit\", \"from\": 2100, \"to\": 2116}, {\"ngram\": \"his bicep\", \"from\": 2163, \"to\": 2172}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The trend caught on with other Olympic swimmers, such as Michael Phelps and Ryan Lochte.\", \"from\": 2175, \"to\": 2263, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2232, \"end\": 2246, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4383334817758688e-35, \"text\": \"Michael Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\"}, {\"begin\": 2251, \"end\": 2262, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryan_Lochte\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ryan Lochte\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryan_Lochte\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ryan_Lochte\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The trend\", \"from\": 2175, \"to\": 2184}, {\"ngram\": \"other Olympic swimmers\", \"from\": 2200, \"to\": 2222}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Eventually, other sports began to get the tattoo as well, with Olympians Nevin Harrison and American canoe sprinter and gymnast Jordan Chiles both debuting ring tattoos.\", \"from\": 2264, \"to\": 2433, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2337, \"end\": 2351, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nevin_Harrison\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nevin Harrison\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nevin_Harrison\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nevin_Harrison\"}, {\"begin\": 2356, \"end\": 2364, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999966896962125, \"rank\": 1.6902190944410343e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2392, \"end\": 2405, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jordan Chiles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"other sports\", \"from\": 2276, \"to\": 2288}, {\"ngram\": \"both debuting ring tattoos\", \"from\": 2406, \"to\": 2432}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Another classic souvenir for the Olympics is specifically reserved for those who place first, second, or third in their respective events.\", \"from\": 2435, \"to\": 2573, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Another classic souvenir\", \"from\": 2435, \"to\": 2459}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2464, \"to\": 2476}, {\"ngram\": \"their respective events\", \"from\": 2549, \"to\": 2572}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During medal ceremonies, and in the celebrations after, fans may notice that the athletes appear to be biting their medals.\", \"from\": 2574, \"to\": 2697, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"medal ceremonies\", \"from\": 2581, \"to\": 2597}, {\"ngram\": \"the celebrations\", \"from\": 2606, \"to\": 2622}, {\"ngram\": \"fans\", \"from\": 2630, \"to\": 2634}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 2651, \"to\": 2663}, {\"ngram\": \"their medals\", \"from\": 2684, \"to\": 2696}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The habit, which Olympians including Sarah Bacon and Kassidy Cook have participated in, is technically a relic of the past, as biting gold was an old way of determining whether or not a piece of gold was real.\", \"from\": 2699, \"to\": 2908, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2736, \"end\": 2747, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Bacon\", \"score\": 0.9999783626862015, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sarah Bacon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Bacon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Bacon\"}, {\"begin\": 2752, \"end\": 2764, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kassidy_Cook\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kassidy Cook\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kassidy_Cook\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kassidy_Cook\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The habit\", \"from\": 2699, \"to\": 2708}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympians\", \"from\": 2716, \"to\": 2725}, {\"ngram\": \"a relic\", \"from\": 2802, \"to\": 2809}, {\"ngram\": \"the past\", \"from\": 2813, \"to\": 2821}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 2833, \"to\": 2837}, {\"ngram\": \"an old way\", \"from\": 2842, \"to\": 2852}, {\"ngram\": \"not a piece\", \"from\": 2879, \"to\": 2890}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 2894, \"to\": 2898}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gold is softer than other medals so if you bite into it and your teeth marks are visible, it is more likely that the medal is actual gold.\", \"from\": 2909, \"to\": 3047, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Gold\", \"from\": 2909, \"to\": 2913}, {\"ngram\": \"other medals\", \"from\": 2929, \"to\": 2941}, {\"ngram\": \"your teeth marks\", \"from\": 2969, \"to\": 2985}, {\"ngram\": \"the medal\", \"from\": 3022, \"to\": 3031}, {\"ngram\": \"actual gold\", \"from\": 3035, \"to\": 3046}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, athletes now mostly bite their medals out of tradition - and not because of the medal content.\", \"from\": 3049, \"to\": 3152, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 3058, \"to\": 3066}, {\"ngram\": \"their medals\", \"from\": 3083, \"to\": 3095}, {\"ngram\": \"tradition\", \"from\": 3103, \"to\": 3112}, {\"ngram\": \"the medal content\", \"from\": 3134, \"to\": 3151}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Most of thecurrent Olympic medals actually are 90 percent silverwith around six grams of real gold.\", \"from\": 3153, \"to\": 3252, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"thecurrent Olympic medals\", \"from\": 3161, \"to\": 3186}, {\"ngram\": \"around six grams\", \"from\": 3222, \"to\": 3238}, {\"ngram\": \"real gold\", \"from\": 3242, \"to\": 3251}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This year, the medals also contain a tiny piece of the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 3253, \"to\": 3321, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the medals\", \"from\": 3264, \"to\": 3274}, {\"ngram\": \"a tiny piece\", \"from\": 3288, \"to\": 3300}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 3304, \"to\": 3320}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One of the more specific traditions seen during the Olympics this year involved the rugby players, who were seen swapping their shorts.\", \"from\": 3323, \"to\": 3458, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the more specific traditions\", \"from\": 3330, \"to\": 3358}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 3371, \"to\": 3383}, {\"ngram\": \"the rugby players\", \"from\": 3403, \"to\": 3420}, {\"ngram\": \"their shorts\", \"from\": 3445, \"to\": 3457}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Normally, following a match, the teams tend to switch jerseys as a signal to the other team of good sportsmanship as if to say, \\\"Good game.\\\"\", \"from\": 3459, \"to\": 3599, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a match\", \"from\": 3479, \"to\": 3486}, {\"ngram\": \"the teams\", \"from\": 3488, \"to\": 3497}, {\"ngram\": \"jerseys\", \"from\": 3513, \"to\": 3520}, {\"ngram\": \"a signal\", \"from\": 3524, \"to\": 3532}, {\"ngram\": \"the other team\", \"from\": 3536, \"to\": 3550}, {\"ngram\": \"good sportsmanship\", \"from\": 3554, \"to\": 3572}, {\"ngram\": \"Good game\", \"from\": 3588, \"to\": 3597}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But this year, Stephen Tomasin from the US rugby team and Rodrigo Isgro from the Argentinian teamswapped shorts.\", \"from\": 3601, \"to\": 3713, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3616, \"end\": 3631, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Tomasin\", \"score\": 0.9999910420111662, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stephen Tomasin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13415036\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Tomasin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Tomasin\"}, {\"begin\": 3641, \"end\": 3643, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9920239494244086, \"rank\": 0.0049751633336552505, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3659, \"end\": 3672, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rodrigo_Isgro\", \"score\": 0.9999967342354132, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rodrigo Isgro\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13415036\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rodrigo_Isgro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rodrigo_Isgro\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After the US lost, Tomasin wanted to honor the tradition of swapping but also wanted to keep his jersey as a memory of competing, according to a representative for the player.\", \"from\": 3714, \"to\": 3889, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3724, \"end\": 3726, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9920239494244086, \"rank\": 0.0049751633336552505, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Tomasin\", \"from\": 3733, \"to\": 3740}, {\"ngram\": \"the tradition\", \"from\": 3757, \"to\": 3770}, {\"ngram\": \"his jersey\", \"from\": 3807, \"to\": 3817}, {\"ngram\": \"a memory\", \"from\": 3821, \"to\": 3829}, {\"ngram\": \"a representative\", \"from\": 3857, \"to\": 3873}, {\"ngram\": \"the player\", \"from\": 3878, \"to\": 3888}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The next best option was to swap shorts instead.\", \"from\": 3890, \"to\": 3938, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The next best option\", \"from\": 3890, \"to\": 3910}, {\"ngram\": \"shorts\", \"from\": 3923, \"to\": 3929}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Join thought-provoking conversations, follow other Independent readers and see their replies Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 3940, \"to\": 4170, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3991, \"end\": 4002, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"score\": 0.9999999998244675, \"rank\": 1.75314505628165e-10, \"text\": \"Independent\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/re